AZERBAIJAN side Sabah FC have confirmed they have parted ways with Pule Ekstein. The club announced the news on their official website claiming that the contract was terminated by mutual consent. "The contract with the South African midfielder was terminated on mutual agreement," the wesbite stated.'The 28-year-old has been working hard for the success of our team this summer. He has scored 3 goals in 16 games he has played this season (13 Premier League, 3 World Cup)."“Sabah” wishes Ekstein good luck in his future career." The former kaizer Chiefs Ekstein joined Sabah late in June and barely six months later, he’s left.